The paper deals with the interpretability of neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of statistical features and natural language to explain the decisions of a neural network suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The fact that the paper focuses on time-series data suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with the reliability of the generated explanations, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
